### Component 3: Backend — Task CRUD Operations

#### [NEW] server/models/Task.js
```javascript
// Schema fields:
{
  user: ObjectId (ref: 'User', required),
  title: String (required),
  description: String,
  status: String (enum: ['pending', 'in-progress', 'completed'], default: 'pending'),
  priority: String (enum: ['low', 'medium', 'high'], default: 'medium'),
  dueDate: Date,
  createdAt: Date (default: now)
}
```

#### [NEW] server/controllers/taskController.js
- **GET /api/tasks** — Get all tasks for authenticated user with **query params**:
  - `?status=pending` — Filter by status (`pending` | `in-progress` | `completed`)
  - `?priority=high` — Filter by priority (`low` | `medium` | `high`)
  - `?sort=-createdAt` — Sort by field (prefix `-` for descending). Options: `createdAt`, `dueDate`, `priority`, `title`
  - `?search=meeting` — Search in title & description (case-insensitive regex)
  - Example: `GET /api/tasks?status=pending&priority=high&sort=-dueDate`
  - Backend builds a Mongoose filter object dynamically from query params
- **POST /api/tasks** — Create new task for authenticated user
  - Validation: title (required, min 1 char), status (must be valid enum), priority (must be valid enum), dueDate (must be valid date if provided)
- **PUT /api/tasks/:id** — Update task (only if owned by user)
  - Validation: same rules as POST, all fields optional
  - Ownership check: `task.user.toString() !== req.user._id.toString()` → 403
- **DELETE /api/tasks/:id** — Delete task (only if owned by user)
  - Ownership check before deletion

#### [NEW] server/routes/tasks.js
- All routes protected with auth middleware
- Validation middleware applied per route
- Route definitions for CRUD operations

